    <field name="scopecontent_teim">Narrowcasting: Technology and the Rise of the Christian Right</field>
    <field name="scopecontent_teim">This video explores the Christian Right's use of a constellation of communication technologies: satellite networks, cable TV, video production, and the internet to achieve their vision for the future, a dark void of democracy. With an in-depth analysis of this theocratic movement by authors Sara Diamond and Fred Clarkson, and activist/researchers Loretta Ross, Chip Berlet and the Rev. Barry Lynn, they point to how stealth campaigning, wedge issues, and "family values are used to navigate the program. </field>
